  "text": "The GCC Internal Compiler Error (ICE) with message 'verify_gimple failed' is traced through the following chain:\n\n1. GIMPLE Verification Implementation (gcc/tree-cfg.cc):\n   - The verify_gimple_in_seq function (line 5244) is the primary entry point for GIMPLE verification of statement sequences. This function calls verify_gimple_in_seq_2 to perform the actual verification.\n   - verify_gimple_in_seq_2 (line 5160) iterates through GIMPLE statements and recursively verifies them, calling verify_gimple_stmt for individual statements.\n   - verify_gimple_stmt (line 5034) dispatches to type-specific verification functions based on statement type (assignments, calls, conditions, etc.).\n   - There is also verify_gimple_in_cfg (line 5443) for verifying GIMPLE in control flow graphs.\n\n2. ICE Handler (gcc/diagnostic-global-context.cc):\n   - The internal_error function (line 776) is the handler that generates the ICE message. When verify_gimple_in_seq detects an error and the 'ice' parameter is true, it calls internal_error with the message '%<verify_gimple%> failed'.\n   - internal_error calls global_dc->diagnostic_impl with diagnostics::kind::ice to report the internal compiler error and then calls gcc_unreachable().\n\n3. Pass Pipeline Integration (gcc/passes.cc):\n   - GIMPLE verification is invoked in passes.cc (lines 2100-2102) after pass execution completes, checking if the function has GIMPLE properties (PROP_gimple).\n   - If PROP_cfg is set, verify_gimple_in_cfg is called; otherwise, verify_gimple_in_seq is called.\n   - This is part of the pass verification infrastructure, not a separate pass in the pipeline.\n\n4. Pass Definition (gcc/passes.def):\n   - The passes.def file defines the pass pipeline structure, though GIMPLE verification is not defined as a separate named pass but rather as part of the pass execution framework infrastructure called after passes complete."
}

